                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 European War 1939/1906: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hamilton</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-10-19T18:00:00+03:00"
                            >October 19, 1943—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 19—10:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1637. Your 1002, October 16, 8 p.m. The British Ambassador has received similar
                    instructions and each of us is addressing a communication to Molotov in
                    accordance with instructions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hamilton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
